column5: Here's just some pic of from the after math of the storm. The fourth pic is a mystery to me. Dinosaur eggs?
Awesome pictures.  Those are weird dem dere dinosaur eggs.  Joey
Those pics are amazing    and those weird shaped things??????   Maybe you are onto something there DSN.LOL
They look like Pterodactyls eggs to me.
Which one? The round ones or the jelly bean shaped ones?  Its weird too you can see right through them.  dsn
very interesting pics,oh and those dino saur eggs are small ice chunks that have been worn away bashing on the rocks and worn smooth just like the rocks on the shoreline.....cheers
amazing pics!!! looks outta this world! hell feezing over maybe? LOL
Ah so thats how they got there huh. Interesting. I was wondering why they look so smooth and round. Hard to picture that they were huge ice chunks before. But it does make sense.  Thanks dsn
Very cool shots.  Ice Storms can be beautiful for pics, but even more so destructive.  Those are amazing pics.

Here's a few from my way...not after this last ice storm, this is from previous storms, the cold weather and spray from Lake Ontario...awesome sights.  Nature can have beauty...even in it's destruction.
ccmtcanada I have seen alot of shoreline ones but found that the sand turns the  m all brown. Yuck!!
Cool pics guys. Ice can be created in some real interesting forms. Thanks.
